post1:
After all this time , the 5 of us still have our meet ups!  We just carry on chatting as though  we met yesterday and it's not just a yearly event. Great friends,  really lucky to be still in touch .
Luckily we're all in Good health... apart from a few old age creaks and cracks.
Already planned next year venue.
post2:
Well the next year is upon us! Yep you're having another birthday... watch out for an influx of children later , and be prepared for a lot of noise.
Just because you're a year older,  doesn't mean you can get a quiet life!
Glad you're my husband...
Happy birthday xxxx  and many more  to come xxxx

post1: Tonight I discovered that if you hang out with a bunch of people who you were friends with in school but haven't seen for approximately.... 30 mumble years...., you will spend a LOT of the time feeling just as awkward as you did when you were a teenager, a LOT of the time comparing your current need for reading glasses and/or perimenopausal symptoms, and a LOT of the time feeling as though you've blocked out half your memories.
